<item>
            <title>[LU-17049] Check supplementary groups for &quot;enable_*_gid&quot; settings</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17049</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;mdt.&amp;#42;.enable_remote_dir_gid&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; parameter is intended to keep advanced functionality out of the hands of users that might abuse them. Typically this is &quot;&lt;tt&gt;0&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (root only) or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-1&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (all users), but it is possible to set a numeric GID to allow sysadmins in a &quot;&lt;tt&gt;wheel&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;admin&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; group to access this functionality on behalf of users. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, it appears that the code that is checking this parameter is only checking the primary GID of the RPC against the parameter, instead of using &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lustre_in_group_p()&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to check all of the supplementary groups of the user, if it is not the primary one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="77574">LU-17049</key>
